name: v3.22.4
body:
- Updated logo (snoo was removed because it is now a reddit trademark).
- Added subscribe/unsubscribe functionality to subreddit feed menus.
- Added contextual selection of subreddit on submit screen.
- Added best sorting preference to front page.
- Added popular to default subreddits.
- Moved view all/search subreddits button to list view.
- Fixed gfycat preview url.

name: v3.21.4
body: - Fixed issue in Android API >= 25 causing widget listview to scroll to top when unintended.

name: v3.21.2
body:
Minor bug fixes & improvements
- Fixed issue with comments not populating in context view.
- Improved login & logout functions. /r/all filters now cleared/synced on login/logout.
- Subreddits list and login/refresh button now updated without restarting activity, when user returns from logging in or out.
- Utility; volume up on preference to test widget auto-refresh.

name: v3.21.1
body: - Various bug fixes

name: v3.21.0
body:
- Added integration with reddits new /r/all filter.
- Added background sync of subs, multis & filters. Triggered daily when subreddit selection activity is opened.
- Added option to open a subreddit in a new activity via post options dialog.
- Added subscription status icon to view all subreddits activity.
- Added score abbreviations to align with reddit scoring change (full score still visible in info panel).
- Various bug fixes.

name: v3.20.2
body:
- Added preview subreddit feature to subreddit search.
- Added open subreddit or domain option to search and temporary feeds.
- Added missing "image" default thumbnail.
- Added utilities section to preferences with cache management.
- Added subreddit selector to search.
- Added archived post checks for voting and comments.
- Added the ability to open temporary multi feeds and browse multihub.
- Added the option to copy a multi to the users account.
- Added experimental stackview widget.
- Changed feed data to file based storage.
- Improved handling of Reddit API errors.
- Fixed issue with comments context dialog height...for good now please (Android bug 5497).
- Fixed handling of "continue this thread" & large comment stubs.
- Fixed issue causing default thumbnail images to have old click listener.
- Fixed NSFW posts displaying default thumbnail.
- Fixed thumbnails flickering in application feed during download.
- See git commit log for more details.

name: v3.18
body:
- Added image sharing and download (long click on image views).
- Added share option to post options dialog.
- Updated library dependencies.
- Various tweaks & fixes, see gitlog for details.

name: v3.17
body:
- Fixed image preview dialog to wrap image height.
- Added new overflow menu icon.
- Added additional theme options and tweaked inbuilt themes.
- Added themes to search, subreddit search & post options dialog.
- Updated markdown editor (beta: enable from preferences).
- Various bug fixes, see gitlog for details.

name: v3.16
body:
- Added context menu for WebView links.
- Added random subreddits.
- Added markdown editor for comments & messages (experimental: enable from preferences).
- Various bug fixes.

name: v3.13
body:
- Share and apply custom themes at /r/reddinator.
- View the default FrontPage when logged in.
- Default Subreddits are now loaded when the user is logged out.
- Various bug fixes and UI enhancements.

name: v3.12
body:
- Added menu to widget.
- Added comments border color and text color to theme options.
- Added comments layout and nested colour scheme preferences.
- Added image previews for i.reddituploads.com images.
- Moved post info in comment context to pull-up panel view.
- Fixed crash when replying to unread messages.
- Fixed bug causing wrong preview image to show for NSFW images.
- Fixed unauthorized error when viewing reddituploads.com URLs.

- Added post info panel to view reddit activity.
- Added viewpager gesture lock to info panel allowing horizontal scrolling when necessary.
- Added action menu to feed activity.
- Added sidebar dialog and feed/sort preferences to feed activity menu.
- Added native comments context dialog.
- Added option to display preview images in app & widget feeds.
- View reddit activity and feed activity can now be opened via url.
- Reddit URLs in comments and messages now open in native views when possible.
- Switched to app-only oauth for logged out api requests.

Fixed bug causing failed login in oauth view by enabling DOM storage (possible Reddit change).
Added suppress changelog flag to suppress the changelog dialog for minor updates.

- Added karma totals and breakdown dialog to account view
- Added username to account menu items and title
- Fixed .gifv malformed url bug in image dialog
- Fixed layout bug causing NPE

- Added image preview dialog
- Updated about dialog with changelog and credits
- Various bug fixes and tweaks

- Native account and message views
- Search for Reddit posts
- Hide posts to your Reddit account when logged in
- Pick theme colours using hex codes
- Huge project clean up (just for the developers sanity)

- Voting on widget feed
- Post option dialogue (widget cogs icon, long press in app feed)
- Domain reddit feeds
- Duplicate post filter (removed duplicates from previous pages)
- Option to hide posts (post filter)
- Various bug fixes and improvements
- Spanish translations

- Added save post feature, saves to Reddit account.
- Lots of bug fixes & improvements.

- Addition of subreddit exclusion filter for /r/all
- Back button preference for better tablet support
- Various bug fixes & improvements.

Another Huge feature release:
- User defined themes!
- Better account integration, loads subreddits & multis on login.
- Subscribe & unsubscribe from Subreddits when an accounts connected.
- Create, edit and browse Multis from your Reddit account!
- New tabs and layouts.
- Submit Links and Text Posts
- Various bug fixes, API & error handling improvements

Switched to OAuth API
Added NSFW tags & default images
Minor fixes
